Uranium exploration junior CanAlaska has promoted Cory Belyk to CEO and executive VP, while Peter Dasler will continue as president of the company. Belyk heads CanAlaska’s exploration and management teams, based from the company’s office in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. Belyk joined CanAlaska in 2019 as COO. Prior to that, he was exploration director for Cameco’s international operations, including Mongolia and Australia. CanAlaska said that the rapid resurgence of interest in the uranium market had accelerated the company’s activities, including the addition of new exploration geologists.